In the year of our Lord 1125, Alexander, king of the Scots, died, and David his brother ascended the throne.
2
However Malcolm, a bastard son of Alexander, attempted to deprive his uncle of the crown, and involved him in two rather severe contests, but David, who was his superior in talent, as well as in wealth and power, defeated him and his party.
