king now held his troops ready for battle, and compelled his officers and the other English nobles to urge forward theworks of the new fortification in which their people were employed with the utmost despatch;
meanwhile Robert saw from his battlements, in deep tribulation, the works which were being carried on against him, and called loudly on his accomplices by name, publicly recommendingthem to adhere faithfully to their traitorous league to which they had sworn.
