Distinguished by the friendship and intimacy of kings and powerful earls, they married noble and fruitful wives, and, surrounded by promising children of both sexes, they were loaded with riches and honours.
Robert became earl of Mellent in the Vexin, as heir to Hugh, his mother Adeline's brother, and in England fortunately received from King Henry a grant of the earldom of Leicester with many other rich favours.
