He was son of William Tête-Hardie, duke of Burgundy, whose father was Duke Reynold, and his mother Adeliza, daughter of Richard II., Duke of Normandy.4
This Guy was the nephew of that cruel Guy, who attempted to seize the duchy of Normandy, and fought at Valesdunes against William the Bastard and Henry, king of France, and stoutly defended Vernon and Brionne.
against them during three years.
