Ralph, seeing the smoke from Pont Echanfré, where he then was, immediately collected troops from all quarters, and hastened to give the enemy battle, for the king had stationed thirty men-at-arms at Sap,8 with as many at Orbec, to check the inroads of the freebooters, who assembled from all parts to pillage the country.
