and, unless this castle had offered them a near asylum, they would have suffered greater loss.
Not long afterwards, this same brave knight made an amicable appeal to the king, humbly representing the advantages of his only showing himself before Fresnel, the garrison of which were as cowardly as they were trouble­ some.
